VS CODE -IDE for angular application development 

Node js- npm (node package manager) -used for install packages, Node comnnd pomt
 check node version after install use this command : node -v
 check npm version after install use this command : npm -v

install angular cli package: goto web and search angular cli npm and install it
 npm install -g @angular/cli
 it will provide set of commands and packages to develop agular application like project create ,   component ..
 check angular cli version / angular project version as: ng version
 ng new		--create angulat application
 ng generate	--creates cangular components,module, services, directive, pipe, interface, class ...
 ng build	--build th angular application
 ng serve	--run the angular application


install Typescript package: goto web and search typescript npm : npm i -g typescript
 by usin this we can write code in angular
 it conatis typescript compiler , used to compile ts code to js code to underdtand by browser
 we can check typescript version by : tsc -v

--------------------------------------------------------------------

npm install -- used to install packages avaliable in packages.json into node_module flder
packages.json -- contains all packages name and versions to develope anular app
ng serve -- to run the application in local
http://localhost:4200/  ---open to open in browser








